<p>PRESS-FORM-PLUS-II that supports reverse engineering enables a direct reference to NASTRAN-format analysis results of sheet metal forming simulations. Thus, it can improve the precision of transformation at the initial stage of design. It also enables the use of point cloud data in the form of STL data, provided that the data have been measured by a non-contact measurement device. Thus, it quickly displays tryout results.</p><p><br></p><h2 class="fr-text-bordered">Features</h2><p align="center"><img src="/uelthai/_content_html_editor_upload/images/DE30388F-CF23-8576-57F5-B779B1AC995B.jpeg" width="530" height="700" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p data-f-id="pbf" style="text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;">Powered by <a href="https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1" title="Froala Editor">Froala Editor</a></p>